</bookmark><comment>mw made "hyphenation..." a two level entry</comment>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="hid/SID_ENABLE_HYPHENATION" id="bm_id7241058" localize="false"/>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="hid/.uno:Hyphenate" id="bm_id3153541" localize="false"/>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3159399" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="U" oldref="1">Hyphenation</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3145068" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="2"><variable id="silben"><ahelp hid=".uno:Hyphenate">The <emph>Hyphenation </emph>command calls the dialog for setting the hyphenation in $[officename] Calc.</ahelp>
</variable></paragraph>
<section id="howtoget">
<embed href="text/scalc/00/00000406.xhp#silbentrennungc"/>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3154366" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="3">You can only turn on the automatic hyphenation in $[officename] Calc when the <link href="text/shared/01/05340300.xhp" name="row break">row break</link> feature is active.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3153192" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="U" oldref="4">Hyphenation for selected cells.</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3150868" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="5">Select the cells for which you want to change the hyphenation.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3150440" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="6">Choose <emph>Tools - Language - Hyphenation</emph>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3156441" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="7">The <emph>Format Cells</emph> dialog appears with the <emph>Alignment</emph> tab page open.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3149260" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="12">Mark the <emph>Wrap text automatically</emph> and <emph>Hyphenation active</emph> check boxes.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3153094" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="U" oldref="8">Hyphenation for Drawing Objects</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3148577" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="9">Select a drawing object.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3156285" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="10">Choose <emph>Tools - Language - Hyphenation</emph>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147394" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="11">Each time you call the command you turn the hyphenation for the drawing object on or off. A check mark shows the current status.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
</body>
